China reiterated its "one country, two systems" approach to Taiwan while unveiling its anti-secession law.
MAC Deputy Chairman Chiu Tai-shan criticized Beijing's move as provocative and aimed at justifying a military invasion.
President Chen Shui-bian condemned the proposed law as a threat to regional stability.
Scholars warned of restricted political space and potential arrests for Taiwanese visiting the mainland.
The US and EU opposed China's legislation, urging restraint.
Mainland Affairs Council Chairman Joseph Wu warned of a referendum if Taiwan is forced to accept Beijing's terms.
The Legislative Yuan plans to pass a resolution against China's anti-secession law.
